quran[44]{c,v,t}:
  23,75,"If We did have mercy on them and removed the harm afflicting them, they would still obstinately persist in wandering blindly in their excessive insolence"
  23,76,"We seized them with the punishment, but they did not go low before their Lord; nor will they humble themselves"
  23,77,until We open to them a gate to a harsh punishment in which they will at once be crushed by despair
  23,78,"It is He who has created hearing, sight and hearts for you. What little thanks you show"
  23,79,It is He who dispersed you about the earth and you will be gathered to Him
  23,80,It is He who gives life and causes to die and His is the alternation of the night and day. So will you not use your intellect
  23,81,"However, they say the same as previous peoples said"
  23,82,"They say, ´When we are dead and turned to dust and bones, shall we then be raised again"
  23,83,We and our forefathers were promised this before. This is nothing but the myths of previous peoples!´
  23,84,"Say: ´To whom does the earth belong, and everyone in it, if you have any knowledge?´"
  23,85,"They will say: ´To Allah.´ Say: ´So will you not pay heed?´"
  23,86,"Say: ´Who is the Lord of the Seven Heavens and the Lord of the Mighty Throne?´"
  23,87,"They will say: ´Allah.´ Say: ´So will you not have taqwa?´"
  23,88,"Say: ´In whose hand is the dominion over everything, He who gives protection and from whom no protection can be given, if you have any knowledge?´"
  23,89,"They will say: ´Allah´s.´ Say: ´So how have you been bewitched?´"
  23,90,The fact is that We have given them the truth and they are liars
  23,91,"Allah has no son and there is no other god accompanying Him, for then each god would have gone off with what he created and one of them would have been exalted above the other. Glory be to Allah above what they describe"
  23,92,Knower of the Unseen and the Visible! May He be exalted above all they associate with Him
  23,93,"Say: ´My Lord, if You let me see what they have been promised"
  23,94,"do not then, my Lord, put me among the wrongdoing people!´"
  23,95,We are certainly capable of letting you see what We have promised them
  23,96,Ward off evil with what is better. We know very well what they express
  23,97,"Say: ´My Lord, I seek refuge with You from the goadings of the shaytans"
  23,98,"and I seek refuge with You, my Lord, from their presence.´"
  23,99,"When death comes to one of them, he says, ´My Lord, send me back again"
  23,100,so that perhaps I may act rightly regarding the things I failed to do!´ No indeed! It is just words he utters. Before them there is an interspace until the Day they are raised up
  23,101,"Then when the Trumpet is blown, that Day there will be no family ties between them; they will not be able to question one another"
  23,102,"Those whose scales are heavy, they are the successful"
  23,103,"Those whose scales are light, they are the losers of their selves, remaining in Hell timelessly, for ever"
  23,104,"The Fire will sear their faces, making them grimace horribly in it, their lips drawn back from their teeth"
  23,105,´Were My Signs not recited to you and did you not deny them?´
  23,106,"They will say, ´Our Lord, our miserable destiny overpowered us. We were misguided people"
  23,107,"Our Lord, remove us from it! Then if we revert again, we will definitely be wrongdoers.´"
  23,108,"He will say, ´Slink away into it and do not speak to Me"
  23,109,"There was a group of My slaves who said, \"Our Lord, we have iman, so forgive us and have mercy on us. You are the Best of the Merciful"
  23,110,But you made a mockery of them so that they made you forget to remember Me while you were laughing at them
  23,111,Today I have rewarded them for being steadfast. They are the ones who are victorious.´
  23,112,"He will say, ´How many years did you tarry on the earth?´"
  23,113,"They will say, ´We tarried there for a day or part of a day. Ask those able to count!´"
  23,114,"He will say, ´You only tarried there for a little while if you did but know"
  23,115,Did you suppose that We created you for amusement and that you would not return to Us?´
  23,116,"Exalted be Allah, the King, the Real. There is no god but Him, Lord of the Noble Throne"
  23,117,"Whoever calls on another god together with Allah, has no grounds for doing so at all and his reckoning is with his Lord. Truly the kafirun have no success"
  23,118,"Say: ´My Lord, forgive and be merciful! You are the Best of the Merciful.´"